description: TEHRAN – Taekwondo athlete Arian Salimi of Iran claimed a gold medal  in the 2024 Olympic Games Saturday night.

description: TEHRAN – Iranian freestyle wrestler Amirhossein Zare lost to Georgian Geno Petriashvili in the men’s 125kg final of the 2024 Olympic Games Saturday night.
title: Iran freestyler Zare collects silver in 2024 Olympics

description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper addressed the resumption of the ceasefire talks hosted by Cairo and with the mediation of the U.S., Qatar, and Egypt.
title: American trick to save Israel from revenge

description: TEHRAN – A former commander of Iran’s Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC) says Iran is prepared to deliver a powerful response to the malicious actions of the Zionist regime.
title: Tehran to deliver strong response to Israeli crimes: official

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has congratulated the people and government of Singapore on the country’s National Day.
title: Pezeshkian congratulates Singapore on National Day

description: TEHRAN- The spokesman and deputy head of the public relations office of the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) stated that the Israeli regime assassinated the Hamas leader to create a rift among Shia and Sunni Muslims.
title: Haniyeh’s assassination aimed to sow division among Muslims: commander

description: TEHRAN – Iran's permanent mission to the United Nations has asserted that a retaliatory response to the Israeli assassination of former Hamas chief Ismail Haniyeh in Tehran is inevitable, regardless of ongoing ceasefire talks in Gaza.
title: Retaliatory action for Haniyeh’s killing independent from Gaza truce talks: Iran UN mission

description: TEHRAN- The spokesman for Iran’s Ministry of Foreign Affairs welcomed the formation of an interim government in Bangladesh headed by Muhammad Yunus.
title: Iran expresses support for the interim government in Bangladesh

description: TEHRAN – A senior Iranian cleric has reaffirmed the steadfast support of the Iranian clergy and religious seminaries for Hezbollah and the broader Resistance Front.
title: Iranian clerics reaffirm support for Resistance Front

description: TEHRAN – An informed source has firmly denied any internal disagreements among Iran's top leadership regarding the response to Israel following the assassination of Ismail Haniyeh, a key Palestinian Resistance movement figure in Hamas, in Tehran.
title: Iranian officials united on retaliation against Israel: source

description: TEHRAN - Iran's newly inaugurated President Masoud Pezeshkian has retained Mohammad Eslami as the head of the Atomic Energy Organization of Iran (AEOI), a key position in the country's nuclear program Eslami has been holding since he was first appointed by the late President Ebrahim Raisi in 2021.
title: Pezeshkian retains Atomic Energy chief, appoints key cabinet members

description: TEHRAN– Iran has completed “legal, diplomatic, and media” preparations to carry out “severe and crushing” retaliation against Israel for the assassination of former Hamas chief Ismail Haniyeh, declared Ali Shamkhani, a political advisor to the Leader of the Islamic Revolution and ex-secretary of Iran’s National Security Council.
title: Leader’s aide says ‘severe and crushing’ response to Israel ready

description: TEHRAN - Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has condemned the massacre of al-Tabin School in the Gaza Strip, calling for swift action by the international community and the United Nations to prevent such atrocities by the Israeli regime.
title: Iranian president calls for international action against Israel after Gaza school massacre

description: TEHRAN - Israel’s brutal attack on a Gaza City school housing displaced Palestinians has sparked widespread outrage and condemnation across the world.

description: TEHRAN - A new Israeli massacre on a school in Gaza sheltering the displaced Palestinians has raised major question marks over Tel Aviv’s lack of desire for any ceasefire in the enclave.

description: TEHRAN-The veteran Iranian actor and Tazieh reciter Fathollah Taheri passed away on Friday, August 9, at the age of 73.
title: Veteran actor, Tazieh reciter Fathollah Taheri passes away

description: TEHRAN-The play “Caligula” written by Albert Camus will go on stage at Iranshahr Theater Complex in Tehran from August 18.

description: TEHRAN-The Persian translation of the book “Dancing With Robots” by Bill Bishop has hit the bookstores across the country.

description: TEHRAN- The documentary film "Noqte," which explores the art of Iranian calligraphy, is set to have its world premiere in Russia, presented by the TV BRICS International Media Network. This unveiling marks a significant milestone, as the film will reach audiences across the BRICS+ countries.
title: Documentary “Noqte” on Iranian calligraphy premieres on TV BRICS

description: TEHRAN – Iran men’s sitting volleyball team head coach Hadi Rezaei announced his 12-player squad for the 2024 Paralympic Games in Paris.
title: Iran men’s sitting volleyball team named for 2024 Paralympics

description: TEHRAN – The anti-narcotics police have disbanded a drug trafficking gang in Saravan county, southeastern Sistan-Baluchestan province, Ahmad-Ali Goudarzi, Commander of the Border Police, has stated.
title: Police dismantle drug trafficking gang in southeast
